ğŸ‘‰  recursive call error


class Test {

    static {
        System.out.println("Static Block");
    }

    {
        System.out.println("Instance Block");
    }

    Test() {
        System.out.println("Constructor");
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Main Start");
        new Test();
        new Test();
        System.out.println("Main End");
    }
}

ğŸ‘‰Static Block
 Main Start
 Instance Block
 Constructor
 Instance Block
 Constructor
 Main End

 ğŸ¯ Golden Rule (Interview Line)
 Static blocks execute once during class loading.
 Instance blocks execute every time an object is created.
 Constructors execute after instance blocks.

ğŸ¯ One-Line Interview Rule (VERY IMPORTANT)
Static â†’ Instance â†’ Constructor
Parent first â†’ Child next